# Components — Aakhara (fork of host_page)

Inherits the full Kinetic Observatory component library from `host_page/docs/design/components.md`. Product-specific additions documented here.

## Inherited (use as-is)

- `<OrbitHero />` — full-viewport hero
- `<Gauge />`, `<Dial />`, `<DataStrip />` — for in-app metrics (rep stats: calls/day, close-rate)
- `<FeatureTile />` — glass-surface card
- `<EyebrowLabel />` — uppercase eyebrow
- `<KineticCTA />` — primary button
- `<GridBackdrop />` — observatory grid overlay

## Aakhara-specific (1–2 components)

### `<ArenaHero />`
Replaces `<OrbitHero />` for landing. Shows a stylized earthen-floor arena with a single spotlight (`--color-accent` wheat) and a silhouetted figure mid-practice. Subtle scroll-linked rotation of the spotlight, not the orbital constellation. Reduced-motion: static.

### `<SparringCard />`
In-app component (post-MVP, future): displays a roleplay scenario card — prospect persona, objection difficulty, voice (Hindi/English), expected duration. Glass-surface base from `<FeatureTile />` + `--color-brand` saddle-brown accent border.

## Stack

- React 18, Tailwind 3, shadcn/ui (new-york + neutral)
- `lucide-react` icons
- `framer-motion` for spotlight animation
- `next-themes` for dark-default + light support

## Future surface

When voice-roleplay app launches (out of scope for this skeleton), expect WebRTC integration, audio waveform components (custom — not from upstream), and live STT-transcript display. None of those exist yet.
